cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.DC 

This paper deals with resource allocation in Fog-RAN for IoT applications, which involves networking, artificial intelligence, and system design. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper employs reinforcement learning methods for decision-making, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves learning and optimization, which can be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Furthermore, the paper deals with system design and control, which can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves distributed computing, which can be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
